@node Welcome

@{u}Welcome to the DraCo guide.@{uu}


When reading this guide, please remember:
 @{i}All translation- and typing-errors are intentional 
 and belong to the whole work of art.@{ui} ;-))


During a programer-meeting in Burlafingen near Ulm, Germany I had the
chance to take a look at the new Amiga clone developed by the german
company - MacroSystem.

As you may already know, its name is @{" DraCo " link DraCo-pix/Draco3.jpg/main}.
Two MacroSystem developers presented a proto version of the DraCo on
the meeting.


The included pictures were taken during the meeting by Christian
Gottschling, Frank J. Dürring and me, Lars Eilebrecht. 
Scanning was done by Christian Gottschling rsp. Frank J. Dürring 
with some fine-tuning done by me.
 

I thought some people may like to get some information about the DraCo,
therefore I decided to make this small compilation.
I do not claim that the information provided in this guide is 100% bug-free
or covers every detail of the DraCo, I just want to provide you with
some information about this new Amiga clone.

I hope you like it... :-)


@endnode

